---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Competitor Intelligence" section="competitors">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">03 · Competitive Intelligence</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">Battlecards — <em>three Tier-1 threats + DIY.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Merged from our market research + the v2.0 sales battlecard deck (built from 2,774 call transcripts, Mar 2026). Field-verified intel is flagged 📞. Clerri's 6-month competitive win rate is ~100% — so the real challenge is getting invited into deals <em>earlier</em>, not winning them.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="takeaway">
    <span class="tk-lbl">Bottom line</span>
    <p>Clerri hasn't lost a competitive deal in 6 months where a rival was named — so the real challenge is getting <em>invited earlier</em> (a marketing/demand-gen problem), not winning once you're in. Among platforms: Subscribili (HIGH, DSO deals) and Plan Forward (MED-HIGH, ledger FUD) are the dangerous ones; BoomCloud is the most <em>frequent</em> (30%+ of deals) but beaten 100%. And the competitor that isn't a logo at all — DIY in-house plans — is who you actually lose to, per the CEO.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="competitors"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Progress: <span data-progress-here="competitors">0 / 0</span> evaluation tasks completed</p>

  <div class="callout wine">
    <div class="lbl">The reframe — per the CEO</div>
    <p style="margin:0 0 0.6rem"><strong>Our real competition is DIY in-house plans, not other platforms.</strong> Clerri rarely loses to Subscribili / BoomCloud / Plan Forward — it loses to practices running their own membership programs. That changes who we're actually fighting and how we message: the enemy is "I'll just do it myself," not a rival logo.</p>
    <p style="margin:0"><strong>The wedge:</strong> (1) independent dental plans are technically illegal in most states without proper licensing — rarely enforced, but a real liability, and Clerri's licensing is built-in protection; (2) data shows DIY doctors give away far deeper discounts than Clerri's structured administration. The pitch isn't "we beat BoomCloud" — it's "stop running this yourself before it costs you." This pairs directly with the <a href="/clerri/website">"Fire your insurance company"</a> narrative.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <div class="lbl">📞 The real challenge — per the v2.0 battlecard deck</div>
    <p style="margin:0 0 0.6rem"><strong>Clerri's competitive win rate is ~100% over the last 6 months</strong> — BoomCloud 6/6 closed, Plan Forward 1/1, Subscribili 1 pending, zero closed losses. The deck's own conclusion: <strong>the challenge is getting invited to compete earlier, not winning once you're in.</strong> That makes top-of-funnel awareness + demand gen marketing's #1 mandate here — you win the deals you're in, so be in more of them.</p>
    <p style="margin:0">Field-verified threat levels (Mar 2026): <strong>Subscribili — HIGH</strong> (DSO deals, extreme pricing) · <strong>Plan Forward — MED-HIGH</strong> (analytics DSOs, ledger FUD) · <strong>BoomCloud — MEDIUM but most frequent</strong> (30%+ of competitive deals). Scale note: their deck cites Clerri at <strong>20,000+ providers</strong> vs. our <strong>5,000+ practices</strong> — likely the same thing in different units (providers per practice) <span class="mono" style="color:var(--muted)">(verify)</span>.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- SPEND COMPARISON TABLE -->
  <h2>Estimated competitor monthly marketing investment</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">All figures are <strong>directional estimates</strong> triangulated from funding, employee counts, content output, podcast/conference presence, and B2B SaaS LinkedIn benchmarks ($8+ CPC, $60-200+ CPL). No competitor publishes spend. Use as a relative ranking, not absolute budgeting.</p>

  <div style="overflow-x:auto">
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Competitor</th>
          <th>PPC / mo</th>
          <th>Paid Social / mo</th>
          <th>Content Syndication / mo</th>
          <th>Trade Shows / yr</th>
          <th>Est. Annual Total</th>
          <th>Confidence</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>BoomCloud</strong><br /><span class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">$3.1M ARR · 16 FTE · bootstrapped</span></td>
          <td class="num-cell">$4-8K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$2-5K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$1-3K</td>
          <td>2-4</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$120-180K</td>
          <td><span class="pill pill-grey">Medium</span><br /><span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Podcast-led, light paid</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Pearly</strong><br /><span class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">2,100 practices · ScOp VC backed · RCM-led</span></td>
          <td class="num-cell">$8-15K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$5-12K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$3-6K</td>
          <td>3-5</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$280-450K</td>
          <td><span class="pill pill-grey">Med-Low</span><br /><span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">VC funding implies above-baseline</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>DentalHQ</strong><br /><span class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">$1.4M ARR · 13 FTE · $99/mo</span></td>
          <td class="num-cell">$3-6K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$1-3K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$2-4K</td>
          <td>2-3</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$90-150K</td>
          <td><span class="pill pill-grey">Medium</span><br /><span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Small ARR caps spend</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background:#fef3c7">
          <td><strong>Plan Forward</strong> <span class="pill pill-rose" style="vertical-align:middle">HIGH THREAT</span><br /><span class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">$3.87M raised · 15 FTE · AADOM circuit</span></td>
          <td class="num-cell">$4-9K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$3-7K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$2-5K</td>
          <td>3-5</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$160-280K</td>
          <td><span class="pill pill-grey">Medium</span><br /><span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">AADOM-heavy verified</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background:#fef3c7">
          <td><strong>Subscribili</strong> <span class="pill pill-wine" style="vertical-align:middle">INSIDER THREAT</span><br /><span class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">$4.3M seed · ex-Membersy CEO · Vyne+Darby backed</span></td>
          <td class="num-cell">$10-18K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$8-15K</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$4-8K</td>
          <td>4-6</td>
          <td class="num-cell">$340-560K</td>
          <td><span class="pill pill-grey">Low-Med</span><br /><span style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Capital-fresh + Vyne co-marketing</span></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <div class="lbl">Trade show booth math · anchor numbers</div>
    <p>CDA = $6,150 for 10x10. ADA SciSession = $41.50/sqft (~$4,150 base + corner). ADSO Summit (1,000 attendees, 100+ exhibitors) = $10-25K all-in including travel. Annual trade-show line items above assume avg. <strong>$12-18K all-in per show</strong>.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- BOOMCLOUD -->
  <h2>BoomCloud <em>(Lehi, UT)</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem">
      <div>
        <span class="pill pill-grey">Threat: Medium · Narrative-led</span>
      </div>
      <div data-status="competitor-boomcloud" class="status">
        <select aria-label="Status">
          <option value="not-started">Not started</option>
          <option value="exploring">Exploring</option>
          <option value="in-progress">In progress</option>
          <option value="blocked">Blocked</option>
          <option value="done">Done</option>
        </select>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div>
        <h4>Verified data</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Founder/CEO: <strong>Jordon Comstock</strong> (in dental since 2006)</li>
          <li>Pricing: <strong>$399/mo + $3.50/mo per patient</strong></li>
          <li>Revenue: $3.1M ARR (2024, up from $2.8M)</li>
          <li>Bootstrapped — no disclosed VC</li>
          <li>Positioning: <em>"#1 Dental Membership Software For Dentists Who Actually Go Fee For Service"</em></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Marketing motion</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Heavy content/SEO ("650 SEO-optimized articles/month" claim — likely AI-generated)</li>
          <li>Most visible founder voice in the category — Comstock hosts/co-hosts 3+ podcasts</li>
          <li>Comparison-blog SEO targeting Kleer/DentalHQ alternatives</li>
          <li>Affiliate via Weave</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout zest-hi" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div class="lbl">The Patient Marketplace finding — paper tiger</div>
      <p>ThePatientMarketplace.com gets <strong>2,400 visits/month with 79.6% bounce rate</strong> (Similarweb verified). Built on WooCommerce (literally a WordPress directory). Primary traffic = <strong>paid display ads</strong>. As of research, homepage shows "Platform Update In Progress" — search layer offline. <strong>The narrative is louder than the asset.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout wine" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div class="lbl">Bigger finding — it's not a directory. It's a gated lead-broker form.</div>
      <p>Live inspection (May 2026): the entire "Patient Marketplace" is a single landing page with a <strong>6-field lead-capture form</strong> (name, email, phone, ZIP, dental needs, insurance status) and a <strong>fake countdown timer</strong> (a known dark pattern). Patients cannot browse practices, see plans, or view profiles. They submit data → BoomCloud routes them to one of their paying practices. This is the WooCommerce abuse: each practice is stored as a "product" but the storefront is gated behind a form. <strong>BoomCloud isn't running a marketplace — they're running a lead-broker funnel disguised as one.</strong></p>
      <p style="margin-top:0.75rem"><strong>What this means competitively:</strong> the 79.6% bounce rate makes total sense — patients land, see the form, leave. Their actual conversion rate must be punishingly low. Clerri's browsable directory is structurally different in a way that maps to a different business model entirely (real two-sided platform vs lead broker). This is a clean narrative line for content, sales decks, and DSO conversations.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div class="lbl">📞 Battlecard field intel — win rate 100% (6/6), active migrations coming in</div>
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem"><strong>Field pricing:</strong> ~$350/mo flat + <strong>2.9% + $0.30 Stripe per transaction</strong> (separate, not in the quoted flat fee). At 200+ members this often exceeds Clerri's all-in. <span class="mono" style="opacity:0.7">(field-verified Feb 2026; our older note had $399/mo + $3.50/patient)</span></p>
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem"><strong>FUD they use:</strong> "Clerri takes a cut — we're flat fee, you keep more" · "with Clerri you don't own your plan/patients" · "we were first." They also run Google Ads on <strong>"Kleer" and "Clerri"</strong> brand terms.</p>
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem"><strong>Landmines to lay:</strong> "Who holds your DMPO compliance license — you or the vendor?" (they have none) · "How many records/day can they migrate?" (<strong>10/day limit</strong> = 30+ days for 300 members) · "Since BoomCloud 2.0, how accurate are your renewal dates?" (the upgrade broke data integrity) · "Platform fee + Stripe = your real per-member cost?"</p>
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem"><strong>Counter-FUD:</strong> flat-fee → "2.9%+$0.30 Stripe is revenue share in another format — let's model your true cost." · ownership → "You own your plan + patients; Clerri manages the compliance liability you'd otherwise carry alone." · first → "First ≠ best: ~400 practices / 8-13 staff vs. Clerri's 20,000+ providers and 7 of top 10 DSOs."</p>
      <p style="margin:0"><strong>Marketplace angle:</strong> their deck sells the Patient Marketplace as a strength — but our teardown (above) shows it's a low-traffic gated lead-broker form (2.4K visits, 79.6% bounce). Their tout vs. our receipts = your counter.</p>
    </div>

    <h4>Clerri counter-strategy</h4>
    <div data-section="competitors">
      <label class="task">
        <input type="checkbox" data-track="bc-01-marketplace-teardown" data-section="competitors" />
        <div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Personally teardown ThePatientMarketplace — document UX gaps, broken flows, listing quality</div></div>
      </label>
      <label class="task">
        <input type="checkbox" data-track="bc-02-anti-narrative" data-section="competitors" />
        <div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Draft "What a real patient directory looks like" content piece — implicit BoomCloud comparison</div></div>
      </label>
      <label class="task">
        <input type="checkbox" data-track="bc-03-podcast-counter" data-section="competitors" />
        <div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Out-podcast Comstock — line up the CEO or John on Group Dentistry Now Show + 2 others</div></div>
      </label>
      <label class="task">
        <input type="checkbox" data-track="bc-04-leadbroker-narrative" data-section="competitors" />
        <div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Build the "directory vs lead broker" narrative across homepage hero, DSO sales deck, and earned media pitches</div></div>
      </label>
      <label class="task">
        <input type="checkbox" data-track="bc-05-screenshot-archive" data-section="competitors" />
        <div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Archive screenshots of TPM's gated form + fake countdown timer — receipts for the pitch, dated and timestamped</div></div>
      </label>
    </div>

    <div class="note-block">
      <div class="note-label">BoomCloud evaluation notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
      <textarea data-note="comp-boomcloud" placeholder="What you learned from the teardown, deals you lost/won against them, customer feedback, conquest opportunities..."></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PEARLY -->
  <h2>Pearly <em>(Santa Barbara, CA)</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem">
      <div><span class="pill pill-grey">Threat: Adjacent · Billing-led</span></div>
      <div data-status="competitor-pearly" class="status">
        <select><option value="not-started">Not started</option><option value="exploring">Exploring</option><option value="in-progress">In progress</option><option value="blocked">Blocked</option><option value="done">Done</option></select>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div>
        <h4>Verified data</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Founders: Jeff Cole (CEO), Sean Emmer (CTO), Billy Grokenberger (CS) — ex-Path</li>
          <li>~39 employees (Tracxn) / 11-50 (LinkedIn)</li>
          <li>Funding: minimal disclosed; ScOp VC listed</li>
          <li><strong>2,100+ practices</strong>, 1.6M+ digital statements/month</li>
          <li>Pricing: demo-gated</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Key differentiator</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Membership is <strong>one module of broader RCM/billing suite</strong></li>
          <li><strong>50+ PMS integrations</strong> — deepest in cohort</li>
          <li>"1-day launch" positioning</li>
          <li>Brand line: <em>"It pays to care."</em></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout mint" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div class="lbl">Strategic read</div>
      <p>Pearly is the <strong>least direct competitor</strong> — they sell billing automation broadly, membership is a wedge. But their 2,100+ practice footprint + 50 PMS integrations make them a real account-level threat for cross-sell. Watch account cannibalization, not category displacement.</p>
    </div>
    <div data-section="competitors">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="pearly-01-integration-parity" data-section="competitors" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Audit Clerri Bridge PMS coverage vs Pearly's 50+ — where are we behind?</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="pearly-02-billing-positioning" data-section="competitors" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Sharpen "we're membership-first" positioning vs Pearly's "RCM with membership as wedge"</div></div></label>
    </div>
    <div class="note-block"><div class="note-label">Pearly notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div><textarea data-note="comp-pearly" placeholder="Account-level overlap, where Pearly wins/loses..."></textarea></div>
  </div>

  <!-- DENTALHQ -->
  <h2>DentalHQ <em>(Raleigh, NC)</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem">
      <div><span class="pill pill-grey">Threat: Medium · Price floor</span></div>
      <div data-status="competitor-dentalhq" class="status">
        <select><option value="not-started">Not started</option><option value="exploring">Exploring</option><option value="in-progress">In progress</option><option value="blocked">Blocked</option><option value="done">Done</option></select>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div>
        <h4>Verified data</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Founder/CEO: <strong>Dr. Brett Wells, DDS</strong> (practicing dentist, runs Wells Family Dental)</li>
          <li>Founded 2017 (8 years at $1.4M ARR = slow)</li>
          <li>13 FTE, $1.5M seed (2022) + bootstrapped, $4.3M valuation</li>
          <li>Pricing: <strong>$99/mo per location</strong> (DHQ Pro) or $990/year. 45-day free trial.</li>
          <li>1,000+ practices, 30,000 members (2022 cite)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Weaknesses</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li><strong>Zero G2/Capterra reviews</strong> — "Be the first to review" as of May 2026</li>
          <li>Founder time split with 7-location dental group</li>
          <li>Modest LinkedIn activity from leadership</li>
          <li>Recent Curve Dental integration partnership (Nov 2025) — limited share</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div class="lbl">Strategic read</div>
      <p>DentalHQ is <strong>the price-leader threat at the low end</strong> — any solo or 2-3 location owner pushing back on Clerri pricing lands here. They're the budget option in conquest conversations.</p>
    </div>
    <div data-section="competitors">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="dhq-01-pricing-objection" data-section="competitors" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Build battle card for "DentalHQ is cheaper" objection</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="dhq-02-conquest-content" data-section="competitors" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Clerri already ranks for "DentalHQ alternatives" — double down on comparison content</div></div></label>
    </div>
    <div class="note-block"><div class="note-label">DentalHQ notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div><textarea data-note="comp-dentalhq" placeholder="Pricing objection patterns, win/loss data..."></textarea></div>
  </div>

  <!-- PLAN FORWARD -->
  <h2>Plan Forward <em>(Indianapolis, IN)</em> <span class="pill pill-rose">HIGH THREAT</span></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem">
      <div><span class="pill pill-rose">Most strategically threatening real competitor</span></div>
      <div data-status="competitor-planforward" class="status">
        <select><option value="not-started">Not started</option><option value="exploring">Exploring</option><option value="in-progress">In progress</option><option value="blocked">Blocked</option><option value="done">Done</option></select>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div>
        <h4>Verified data</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Co-CEOs: <strong>Megan Lohman</strong> (ex-dental office mgr), Jane Levy</li>
          <li>Founded 2018, remote-only, 15 FTE</li>
          <li>Funding: $2M Seed B Oct 2023; <strong>$3.87M total</strong>. Elevate Ventures, IU Angel, Revere Partners</li>
          <li>Pricing: demo-gated</li>
          <li>Targets solo + DSO explicitly</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Why HIGH threat</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li><strong>"Read/Write integrations that actually work"</strong> with Dentrix, Eaglesoft, Open Dental, Ascend, Denticon</li>
          <li>Lohman runs AADOM podcast circuit — second-most-visible founder voice</li>
          <li>Publishes <em>"a list of the Clerri alternatives"</em> as defensive SEO</li>
          <li>Direct play for DSO buyers on Henry Schein One stack</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div class="lbl">📞 Battlecard field intel — threat MED-HIGH (deck); win rate 1/1</div>
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem"><strong>⚠️ Their signature FUD — "no ledger write":</strong> Plan Forward intentionally does NOT write to PMS account ledgers, frames it as a design choice, then plants production-reporting doubt about Clerri before your rep can respond. Prospect echoes: "I don't like someone thinking they have a credit on their account" / "when you sell a practice, doesn't ledger write-back reflect poorly on production?"</p>
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem"><strong>Counter-FUD script:</strong> "Recurring membership revenue is a <em>premium</em> to practice buyers, not a liability — it de-risks the practice. Ledger integration captures that revenue accurately in production reports. Plan Forward's approach leaves it outside your PMS, creating reconciliation gaps. Ask your broker which they'd prefer."</p>
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem"><strong>Other tactics:</strong> free <strong>"Membership Assessment"</strong> (temp PMS integration showing member-vs-cash data in 1-2 days — a powerful displacement wedge) · the "DPO administrator = you lose control" claim <strong>(FALSE — retracted in writing under legal pressure from Clerri's CEO)</strong>.</p>
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem"><strong>Landmines to lay:</strong> "How long was onboarding — and time to first enrolled patient?" (Tend took 2 months just on fee alignment) · "Who holds the DMPO license?" (they're not licensed) · "Do they support bilingual English/Spanish staff + patients?" (they don't).</p>
      <p style="margin:0"><strong>Win signal:</strong> Tend (multi-location) is actively evaluating a switch <em>from</em> Plan Forward <em>to</em> Clerri (Mar 2026). <span class="mono" style="opacity:0.7">(Bio to verify: their deck calls Megan Lohman a "dentist/founder"; our note had her as ex-office-manager — confirm before using.)</span></p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout rose" style="margin-top:1rem">
      <div class="lbl">Counter strategy</div>
      <p>(a) Out-podcast Lohman with executive/customer voices on GDN Show + Bulletproof Dental. (b) Publish explicit "read/write integration parity" content aimed at DSO buyers — especially Ascend + Denticon shops. (c) File HSO API Exchange application immediately to neutralize integration moat claim.</p>
    </div>
    <div data-section="competitors">
