    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-top:0.75rem">Not in the battlecard deck at all — its blind spot. But per Jim, Clerri rarely loses to a platform; it loses to "I'll just run it myself." The enemy is inertia + DIY, not a rival logo.</p>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:0.5rem">
      <div>
        <h4>Why practices try it</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>"It's just a spreadsheet + a discount — why pay a platform?"</li>
          <li>No perceived need for compliance/licensing help</li>
          <li>Want to keep 100% of the revenue</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>The wedge (Clerri's win)</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li><strong>Liability:</strong> independent plans are illegal in most states without proper licensing (rarely enforced, but real exposure) — Clerri's DMPO is built-in protection</li>
          <li><strong>Economics:</strong> DIY docs give away far deeper discounts than Clerri's structured administration <span class="mono" style="opacity:0.7">(verify the data point)</span></li>
          <li><strong>Effort:</strong> renewals, billing, compliance filings, churn — all on the practice</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
